	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				After toying with the idea for a while, today I finally embarked upon this quest. First I went to the Temple of Life and hailed the appropriate NPC. He gave me no indication that I was supposed to ask about a shield or grimrot, so I asked the magic phrase &quot;I am here to defend life&quot;, and he then told me to go and do my thing in SK hunting this Grimrot fellow. <BR>
<BR>
I've read these posts so I was expecting it to be a nightmare of waiting. But amazingly not 5 minutes after I get there the live version of Grimrot spawned! What a great turn of events...I buffed up and took him out solo. At level 51 he conned light blue to me...He casts a strength drain that will stick on you a few minutes, but I resisted almost all of them. His pet is a mere annoyance and I swiped him down in 2 swings. <BR>
<BR>
I looted off of him two scythes, one is a NO DROP, the one that you end up turning in in Qeynos. The other is a LORE item that can be sold. Both are named the same thing, so just pick up both and run with it. <BR>
<BR>
I'm still waiting for the undead version to drop and dutifully kill the PH when possible. But it makes for some mundane waiting. Bring lots of food and water, a good book, and every 3 minutes or so kill the PH and wait for Grimrot to spawn. Back to camping I go :)<BR>
<BR>
Rector Honorborne<BR>
51 Paladin of Xev<BR>
&lt;Obsidian Dragon Society&gt;
				</font>
			</td>

