	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				On a server where NoDrop is King, this item has nice stats and can't be PK'd  by an opportunistic brigand.  I have recently undertaken this quest after learning of the Aegis.  3 days effort have raised my faction from dubious to ally and achieved the No Drop Scythe from the Live Grimrot.  Getting the drops takes patience and time (killing everything in sight at the Skele Playground in SK), but the faciton is fast and easy.  Several posts have mentioned the Lashun Novashine &quot;2gp Quest&quot;  and the &quot;Bone Chip Quest.&quot;  These Quests can be combined to obtain 5 factions hits at once everytime you click GIVE.  Lashun takes either 2 gps or 2 bc's at a time and then casts a heal on you.  The secret is to give him several bc's and the 2gp. Here's what you do:<BR>
<BR>
1) Camp the Grimrot spawngrounds in SK, killing &quot;putrid skeletons.&quot; These are the only ones that drop bone chips (as well as certain named spawn nodrop/lore bone chips) and it is from these putrid's that Live and Undead Grimrot eventually spawn.  (Each putrid gives Priests of Life faction but ehe other skele's do not).<BR>
<BR>
2) Collect BC's until you think your eye's will bleed (I had 2 bags full of 20stacks) then port/gate back to Qeynos, stop by the bank for some gold and find Lashun.<BR>
<BR>
3) Open a trade window to Lashun Novashine using 2gp.<BR>
<BR>
4) Then fill each of the 4 open slots above with 2 bone chips per open slot (for a total of 8bc's).<BR>
<BR>
===&gt; You will now have a trade window to Lashun that looks like this:<BR>
<BR>
  _______<BR>
  | 2bc |<BR>
  |-----|<BR>
  | 2bc |<BR>
  |-----|<BR>
  | 2bc |<BR>
  |-----|<BR>
  | 2bc |<BR>
  |-----|<BR>
  | 2gp |<BR>
