	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok... for you dark and evil races, there is a way to get faction that actually works and gives pretty good exp.  Im a lvl 47 DE cleric on vallon zek (pvp server).  I spent a massive amount of time camping Lord Grimrot and so far all i have it the decaying heart or whatever it is from the dead version,  i killed about 500 bandits during that time and it didnt do anything to my faction (i spent lvl 20-25 killing treants).  I then went to qeynos hills because i was sick of south karana.  I then proceded to kill gnolls in blackburrow for a vast amount of time. 300-400 dead gnolls later and many pk attempts on my life i found that my faction has still yet to increase with the guards of qeynos.  I then follow guard cheslin around qeynos hills and picked up the cards he dropped and gave them to him.  I did that twice and the faction with the guards increased from &quot;ready to attack&quot; to &quot;threateningly&quot;.  While i was following cheslin, i killed many rabid wolfs and grizzlies and had about 3 rabid grizzly pelts and 12 rabid wolf pelts.  So i used an invis potion and went into the temple of life.  They werent kos but &quot;dubious&quot;.  After i gave all the putrid pelts from the rabid animals to Preistess Caulria my faction went up to indifferent.  I went back out to qeynos hills and got about the same amount of rabid wolf and bear pelts, invised myself and turned in the pelts and when all was finished, i was amiable to the temple of life and gained a blue bubble of exp(pretty good for lvl 47).  I then talked to Camlend and he would talk back, but i am not fully ready for the quest yet, make sure he tells you exactly what to do for the quest or he wont accept the scythe and heart from grimrot.  hope it helps and sorry it took so much space.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
